<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="533" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/281a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-06">August 6, 1938</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>43. Stand by for detailed instructions. Proviso to concession on balsa
                            timber absolutely necessary. If agreement already signed, exchange of
                            notes necessary. If agreement not signed, proviso should be inserted in
                            schedule II.</p>
                        <p>To facilitate further instructions, telegraph that agreement has been
                            signed if that is the case.<note n="21" xml:id="d533fn21">The Minister
                                in Ecuador in telegram No. 91, August 6, 2 p.m., stated that the
                                agreement had been signed that morning (611.2231/278).</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>